spanGrp.span: Spanish translation by Eulogio Ibaez Noza; English translation by Franoise Rose | transcription Eulogio Ibaez Noza
Good afternoon, Francisca, today is the 1st of September, I am going to talk with you, I am going to tell you.
kopereoopo Pransiska , juiti sache etona setiembre ; nechjirikwoyre pyee mmetokowyore to ...
Buenas tardes Francisca, hoy da 01 de septiembre, voy a conversar contigo, voy a contarte
There was a boy, at night, the moon was bright.
emjaai ma mperu , te yoti tjraku to koje
haba un muchacho, en la noche, con una luna clara
And he plays in the company of a little dog.
And there is also a small toad.
And at dawn (lit. when it was light), he peeped into the dwelling place of the small toad.
ene te tjaraipo ee ... majinokpo to towrisraai to sapgira
y cuando amaneci el nio espi donde estaba (vivia ?) el sapito
And it was not there, it had gone.
y ya no estaba, ya se habia ido
After that, he played again with his small dog.
takepo tyutsaru ... tyutsaruwre , makochane to pakgira
despus (juega) volvi a jugar junto con el perrito
And the small dog also went to the door.
ene to pakgira tomuire tyompo te ... te tapajo
y el perrito tambin se fue a la puerta
And after that, the small dog fell.
y despus se cay el perrito
And he (the boy) went out and took the small dog in his arms, he took it.
ene ema tyuchkopo ene mayookopo to ... to pakgira mavepo
y l se sali y lo alz al perrito, lo agarr
After that, the small dog too went outdoors and it played, it went running.
takepo to pakgira tomuire tyuchkopo te neko ene tyutsaru tyono tjunopopuiko
accent: tjnopopuko pas clair si j = accent secondaire ou 2me accent primaire
despus el perrito tambin se sali afuera y juega, se va corretea
And it jumped on the bees' nest (lit. the living place of the bees);
ene taetereucho to towrisra to janiono
y saltaba donde estaban (vivian ?) los petos
And it tried hard, he wanted to touch it, the dog jumped again.
ene ta... ta... takomesajiiko , tawooo tayjtokyore teterekojno to paku
y buscaba la forma de tocarlo, saltaba otra vez el perro
Then they stung the small dog.
tak ... takepo tayukpo to ... to pakgira
And the little boy saw the bees.
ene ma moperugra ee ... muemopo to janiono
y el niito vi a los petos
And he lied (on the ground) so that they wouldn't sting him, you see ?
y se tendi (se ech) para que no le piquen, no?
And the bees following the small dog were numerous.
ene movera to janiono , tapono to pakgira
y haban muchos petos que persiguieron al perrito
And there was also an owl looking at it.
ene ( to ) etjooi to yusa to... tomuire taemoorookooi
y haba un buho tambin le estaba mirando
and it (the owl) also went flying to see the boy.
ene tomuire tyoropooi taemo ma moperu
y tambin iba volando para verlo al nio
After that, the boy went up on an anthill, a big anthill.
takepo ma... ma moperu tyopnopo te to kjaeisi , chope kjaeisi
despus, el nio se subi en el hormiguero, hormiguero grande,
And he searched for his little dog, he was calling it shouting.
ene matankopo to ... mayee pakgira mapiookogierekooi
y le busc a su perrito le estuvo gritando
Then a deer came out and now it looks like it went hoisting the boy.
tak ... takepo , tyuchjikpo to kjowo , ene kuti te to tayookopripo ma moperu
despus sali el ciervo y como que lo llev alzandolo al nio
And it (the deer) ran and took him (the boy) to the riverbank, he (the boy) held (himself) onto the deer's antlers.
ene tyjunopopo tomo te tachochoku to kjokre , ema tkootokwoprii te to tajiu to kjowo
y corri (el ciervo) lo llev (al nio) a la orilla del ro en su cuerno (asta) del ciervo
And the little dog saw him, and followed him, running (all along) too.
ene to pakgira taemopo ene tapompo tomuire tyjunopoprii
tomuire sounds like tomue (apocope ? final-syllable dropping ? flap not pronounced ?)
y el perrito lo vi (al nio) y se fu detrs de l, tambin corriendo
After that, the deer threw him (the boy) into the water, the little dog also went to the water
takepo to kjowo tagopo te to une , tomuire to pakgira tyompo te to une
despus el ciervo lo lanz (al nio) al agua, tambin el perrito se fu al agua
well, now, there are no more bees.
bueno ahora ya no estn los petos
Then the water was shallow and the small boy did not drown, he caught his dog and kept it in his arms.
takepo wo topeno to une ene ma moperugra wo teegia makootokpo to mayee paku ene mayookopo
despus no estaba profunda el agua, el niito no se ahog, lo cogi a su perro y lo alz
Then they went to the bank and they look whether there weren't bees on the riverbank.
takepo tyonompo te tachochoku , ene jio ... najinokpo jee tajinapka to janiono te to tachochoku to... to kjokre
jio is an error, corrected with the next word.
despus se fueron a la orilla y observaron si no estaban los petos en la orilla del ro
After they were resting on a big tree on the riverbank.
takepo tnarakongierekooi te to chopegie wkugi te tachochoku to kjokre
despus estaban descansando en un grueso tronco de arbol en la orilla del ro
And there was a small toad there.
ene etjooi to sapgira te pjuena ,
Well, at first, there were two.
takepo tyuch ... ee ... tyuchkuompo to pomriono sapgirano
And it pleased it (the small toad) that the boy was there, because it was the friend of the boy, the small toad.
ene torikooi to emjaai ma moperu tajicho ee ... taemnaksarerii ma moperu to... to sapgira
y le agradaba (el sapito) que este (all) el muchacho aqui porque era su amigo, el muchacho (0), el sapito (S).
Then the small boy caught a small toad and he put it in his hand.
takepo ma moperugra makootokpo to et ... etona sapgira , ene ma... manokpo te to mawupe
initial e of ene is hardly audible
despus el niito agarr un sapito, l lo puso en la mano
And he called the other toads.
ene muechopo to pomri , pomri sapgirano
y los llam a los otros sapitos
The small toads were watching him, there were numerous the toads watching him.
los sapitos lo estaban mirando (al nio),
This is what I have been saying, ladies and gentlemen, this I want you all to know.
eto mmetokooi tatanoviono , memenoviono , pjoka nwooo to ( n ) echa .
the speaker says necha, but when doing the transcriptin, corrected it as echa (intended meaning).
eso estoy diciendo Seores y Seoras, esto quiero que sepan
